    <item>
      <title>Arduino Robust Serial</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/project/arduino-robust-serial/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 26 Oct 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/project/arduino-robust-serial/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Robust Arduino Serial&lt;/strong&gt; is a simple and robust serial communication protocol. It was designed to make two Arduinos communicate, but can also be useful when you want a computer (e.g. a Raspberry Pi) to communicate with an Arduino.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please read the 
&lt;a href=&#34;https://medium.com/@araffin/simple-and-robust-computer-arduino-serial-communication-f91b95596788&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Medium Article&lt;/a&gt; to have an overview of this protocol.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Implementations are available in various programming languages:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Arduino (&lt;code&gt;arduino-serial/&lt;/code&gt; folder)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/araffin/python-arduino-serial&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Python&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/araffin/cpp-arduino-serial&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;C++&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/araffin/rust-arduino-serial&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Rust&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
